<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I apologize for this post being a bit off topic, and I would have posted it on a more off topic board here, but lets be honest they get about as much action as a widowed grandma. <P>On a more serious note, I&#8217;d like to introduce Neverwinter Nights to those of you who have never heard of it (Those of you that have well read on and drool with me).<P>  I have been reading a lot about people&#8217;s complaints on various forums about the current online role-playing games inability to keep them happy in general.  I think Neverwinter Nights is the solution to 99% of the problems of today&#8217;s multiplayer CRPG&#8217;s.<P>1.	Have you ever wished that the whole world or dungeon could be your group&#8217;s private area? Well wish no more Neverwinter Nights supports from solo to 64 players at once. This covers everything one likes doing from solo play to large raids, yet does not make for an overcrowded world. Of course the DM will need a cable modem or better to support the 64 players, but that&#8217;s not all that uncommon nowadays.<P>2.	No camping ever again. Yep, you heard it. These will be dungeon crawls. What you say? &#8220;What&#8217;s a dungeon crawl?&#8221; Well me boyo having played these current online games now I&#8217;m not surprised you don&#8217;t know. It&#8217;s actually clearing a dungeon from top to bottom, not camping one part for hours on end.<P>3.	Do you ever have that feeling that your life has no purpose? I don&#8217;t blame you. In a world where heroes out number commoners 10 to 1 that is to be expected. O and Not to mention that orc camp you and your fellow heroes just killed will be back in 6 minutes and 34 seconds. In Neverwinter Nights, this is a thing of the past. World&#8217;s are built with the prospective of one group of people being there, as such respawning is not needed. It also gives you a since of accomplishment. For once you can think to yourself wow maybe I made a difference in the world.<P>4.	What about boredom? In other words &#8220;Man I&#8217;m sick of killing these gnolls in South Karana for hours on end.&#8221; Well be bored no more me bucko. In Neverwinter Nights worlds are built by players for players. In other words there is gonna be endless different places to explore and adventure in.<P>5.	&#8220;Wow, worlds built by players?!?&#8221; Indeed grasshopper, just as one put whisky in mouth to forget ugly wife you must forget notion of worlds built by a company with only $$$ in their mind. Neverwinter Nights offers almost limitless boundaries in building worlds. Don&#8217;t like how Lower Guk etc. is set up now build your own all the way down to the critters and what they do in their spare time. Of course, if your not feeling to inspired you can but together a generic dungeon in about 20 min.<P>6.	&#8220;So cool what about quests and stuff?&#8221; Much different young sparrow. Chicken doesn&#8217;t like being send all over world to come back and receive one piece of corn more then the next fowl. In Neverwinter Nights the DM alters the plot and rewards you or punishes you for every action you take.<P>7.	&#8220;Neato that must make role-playing rewarding and fun.&#8221; Ahh my child the way of the Chicken is becoming known to you. In NWN the DM can possess and take control of any NPC in the game thus giving background and feeling to your surroundings. <P>8.	&#8220;Hmm, but wait what if I get a L33T D00D DM or players?&#8221; Ahh many questions good, good. The glory is that you not stuck with them simply move to a different world or if you&#8217;re the DM boot them. Your character is not frozen on a server like in games right now.<P>9.	&#8220;What of PvP or the griefers that sometimes plague it?&#8221; Ahh chicken defecates in contempt on greifers then scratches eye out to eat. MMM very good BAGOK! In NWN DM&#8217;s can choose to allow or disallow PVP. Also for you L33t paladins (or whoever goes against what you are supposed to be) who think they can go about killing whatever when you supposed to be good don&#8217;t be surprised if the god&#8217;s smite you.<P>10.	&#8220;What about balance? Will some classes be uber or some suxxor?&#8221; *smack*  Never use those words in the presence of chicken again, or ye eyes are me lunch. Back to the question ahem. NWN uses AD&D rules right from the book one of the oldest and most respected gaming systems ever. It has been refined for almost 30 years and is gonna be about as balanced as it can possibly get.<P>Well there you have it folks. I can&#8217;t think of anything else now and since 10 is a nice round number, I&#8217;ll leave it at that. If I think of more I&#8217;ll put it up. Tell me you anit drooling. Check out more at <A HREF="http://www.neverwinternights.com" TARGET=_blank>www.neverwinternights.com</A>  <P>Disclaimer: Lol no I don&#8217;t work for them I&#8217;m just a rabid fan from what I&#8217;ve seen so far. The goofyness? Well I&#8217;m just in a goofy mood.<BR>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
