<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by cerios:<BR><STRONG>From what I have seen the "classical" dungeon crawl wont really be anymore possible then in EQ, besides third person view sucks bobo. If you have some more details shoot, but as of now I don't think NWN is what most of us are looking for.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P><BR>Why do you say that? The creatures in AD&D are much more balenced then in eq and such. For example, using eq terms even cons really are an even fight, green really are trivial etc. Moreover, creatures won't respawn unless the DM sets them up to. This really forces you to move on. I don't think people camp because they want to I think it is because they are forced to do to safety reasons which is due to overpowered monsters and bad pathing.<P>I agree about the 3rd person view. I'm not a big fan of it either, but considering how good everything else is looking I can look past it. Not to mention the whole game is 3d so I wouldn't be suprised if they offer a patch that makes it 1st person if they get alot of requests. They are already setting it up so that you can zoom and move around the camera. Going from 3rd to 1st person view anit hard to do in fully 3d games. All it is a matter of is switching the camera view and moving the interface around to accomodate the new view.
