<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Sybert Screwloose:<BR><STRONG>I'm familiar with NWN but I don't know too much about it.  How do they plan to stop a DM from setting up a game that is just one giant room full of treasure for his or her  friends to get rich?  Or from rigging a dungeon with super easy monsters that give a ton of experience?</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>They are planning on setting up a Character Vault where you will store your character when your not playing him. Also to keep offical status the character can only gain so much xp or treasure over a givin time. For example, if your character is gone for 4 hours they will calculate based on your level how much xp or treasure you could have reasonably gotten in that amount of time. The DM can also set up rules against or boot players they feel are inappropriate. You are also not obligated to play with anyone cheating either, simply move to a new world.
