<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sounds like a MUD... Nothing innovating here<P>One more thing, be prepared for "hacked" characters to enter your world  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Just trying to play devils advocate here.. But seriously though, I have done all that when I used to run various MUDS. This is the same thing except its graphic and not text.<P>I'm sure it will sell well, but I think the majority of people playing MMORPGs wont switch to something that has 10-100 people in it (more like 50 people which is typical on a MUD).  The novelty of "creating your own world" wears off quick because its not as easy as most people think  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  A quake server is one thing (no depth, easy to create), but setting up a good RPG is tough.  And with pre-packaged gfx they will all look the same.
</FONT>
