<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'd like to mention that the 64 player limit is per 'software server', meaning that with several of these running per machine, they are equivalent to EQ zones.  With campaigns having many zones linked together that means the real limit is (64 PER zone * number of zones * hardware servers linked together).<P>Several roleplaying groups already have the beta version of the campaign editors, and are well on their way to re-creating whole campaign worlds.<P>____________________<P>The advantage Neverwinter Nights will have over the competition is its ability to be played as a stand alone game.  It comes with a Baldur's Gate sized campaign  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">.<P>With many fansites(and official sites as well) offering homebrewed campaigns/dungeouns/modules for download, anyone with the game will have near instant access to possibly hundreds of game modules to play solo, over a LAN with friends, or through the official NWN match-making servers.
</FONT>
