I don't know how others feel, but NWN sounds like it might actually work.  Sure, you can cheat and get a high level character quickly, but it doesn't amount to much.  The challenge is what is fun.  If I can get the challenge, I will be happy to stay level one for weeks or months.<P>The challenge is what I found lacking in EQ.  There doesn't seem to be much of a middle ground.<P>One concern:  Is death a problem?  If death carries little penalty, like EQ, then some of the challenge is gone.  If it carries a big penaly, how do you deal with GM's who create killer worlds?<P>--------------------<P>Josef - Servant of Balance
