<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
THE problem with NWN going first person is poly count.  The level of detail in NWN models and such is pretty high compared to EQ.  If you were to give the user the ability to look out over the horizon, your poly count would skyrocket and become unmanagable.  The devs I believe have addressed this question and that was the basic answer.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by cerios:<BR><STRONG>The reason that they would have difficulty going to first person view is that there would be a ton of visual artifacts that would be left over(tons of areas that didn't look quite right) not to mention the fact that the engine is no more true 3D then EQ, it won't handle up and down very well. For a time I seriously considered puttng together a half dozen servers to create my own world but really this does not look that practical.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>--------------------<P> <IMG SRC="http://www.kansas.net/~brian/sig.jpg"> 
